1
00:00:05,573 --> 00:00:07,594
Previously on Prison Break:

2
00:00:07,733 --> 00:00:09,661
There's something
about this guy.

3
00:00:09,799 --> 00:00:12,239
It's like he knows where we're
going and what we're thinking.

4
00:00:12,245 --> 00:00:13,760
If that's true,
it's just a matter of time

5
00:00:13,790 --> 00:00:15,719
before he finds out
about the money in Utah,

6
00:00:15,811 --> 00:00:17,172
our way into Mexico...

7
00:00:17,265 --> 00:00:18,341
Everything.

8
00:00:24,077 --> 00:00:26,808
...have an attorney present
during questioning...

9
00:00:26,901 --> 00:00:28,308
Caroline, they're
taking her in.

10
00:00:28,405 --> 00:00:29,900
Of course.
I'll keep an eye on her.

11
00:00:30,043 --> 00:00:31,680
I did it, Dad.

12
00:00:31,771 --> 00:00:33,468
Just do as you're told.

13
00:00:33,556 --> 00:00:37,144
Otherwise there will be consequences
that will affect us all.

14
00:00:37,239 --> 00:00:39,012
My dad's an Air Force colonel.

15
00:00:39,157 --> 00:00:41,600
When I told him I was
staying in a hotel with

16
00:00:41,696 --> 00:00:45,372
a guy that I maybe sorta liked,

17
00:00:45,695 --> 00:00:47,191
he lost it.

18
00:00:47,567 --> 00:00:49,441
What are you doing here?
Where's Maricruz?

19
00:00:49,535 --> 00:00:50,893
She's with me now.

20
00:00:51,016 --> 00:00:53,981
- Don't push it.
- Hey, Fernando, slow down, man.

21
00:00:54,035 --> 00:00:57,043
I was trying to tell you,
the wedding is in Vegas.

22
00:00:59,125 --> 00:01:01,671
- Which one of them was it?
- Might be Scofield.

23
00:01:01,767 --> 00:01:04,063
Probably gonna find his
brother in there, too.

24
00:01:05,136 --> 00:01:08,051
- Where to, sir?
- Utah.

25
00:01:16,198 --> 00:01:18,970
This morning,
authorities in Illinois issued an update

26
00:01:19,068 --> 00:01:22,791
on the escaped convicts known
until now as the Fox River Eight.

27
00:01:22,886 --> 00:01:25,472
Chicago mob boss John
Abruzzi was gunned down

28
00:01:25,546 --> 00:01:27,850
outside a Washington D.C.
motel last night

29
00:01:27,996 --> 00:01:31,002
after investigators received
a tip from an informant.

30
00:01:31,148 --> 00:01:35,222
The other seven escapees are still
at large and considered dangerous.

31
00:01:39,578 --> 00:01:42,252
I didn't think Abruzzi'd
be the first to go.

32
00:01:42,355 --> 00:01:44,941
I have a feeling we're in
for lots of surprises.

33
00:01:45,435 --> 00:01:48,663
They said seven are still out there.
So much for faking our deaths.

34
00:01:49,077 --> 00:01:51,661
I bought us some time--
that's what counts.

35
00:01:54,225 --> 00:01:57,471
- How much further?
- 70, 80 miles.

36
00:01:57,566 --> 00:01:58,032
Good.

37
00:01:58,125 --> 00:02:00,683
Means we should be hitting the
Double K Ranch by this afternoon.

38
00:02:00,757 --> 00:02:02,751
Or we can keep driving,
pick up LJ and hit Panama.

39
00:02:02,777 --> 00:02:03,751
We can't hit Panama!

40
00:02:03,896 --> 00:02:06,810
We can't hit anything!
We can't do anything without the money.

41
00:02:06,908 --> 00:02:09,251
We need to find
Charles's stash.

42
00:02:11,066 --> 00:02:14,120
I know some other guys who
are thinking the same thing.

43
00:02:16,206 --> 00:02:22,152
The money is buried under a
silo at the Double K Ranch

44
00:02:22,248 --> 00:02:25,300
just outside of Tooele, Utah.

45
00:02:25,408 --> 00:02:28,932
There's $5 million there.

46
00:02:44,567 --> 00:02:48,621
Oh. Um, you know,
when I was in Cheyenne,

47
00:02:48,766 --> 00:02:50,821
I pulled my ticket
out of the bag.

48
00:02:50,925 --> 00:02:52,333
It tore in half, and...

49
00:02:52,467 --> 00:02:54,721
I have no idea what
happened to the other part.

50
00:02:55,236 --> 00:02:56,693
They didn't issue
you a replacement?

51
00:02:56,918 --> 00:02:59,502
No. The young lady-- I think--
her name was Sherry--

52
00:02:59,645 --> 00:03:03,183
she actually said that this half is
okay because the bar code is on it.

53
00:03:03,277 --> 00:03:05,293
Well, you really need
the whole ticket.

54
00:03:05,437 --> 00:03:07,972
This is exactly what
I was trying to avoid.

55
00:03:08,075 --> 00:03:10,090
She said that everything
would be fine because...

56
00:03:10,236 --> 00:03:11,781
That's okay. It'll do for now.

57
00:03:11,966 --> 00:03:15,071
But make sure you ask for a
replacement when you get to Provo.

58
00:03:15,218 --> 00:03:17,753
I definitely will. Thank you.

59
00:03:18,496 --> 00:03:21,413
- It's always something, uh?
- Oh, God, I know.

60
00:03:33,218 --> 00:03:35,472
I don't wanna go home.

61
00:03:37,238 --> 00:03:39,340
I wish we could keep driving.

62
00:03:39,445 --> 00:03:42,360
I don't think your Pops
will be down for that.

63
00:03:42,866 --> 00:03:45,260
Wouldn't it be fun?

64
00:03:45,878 --> 00:03:48,081
We could go to...

65
00:03:48,216 --> 00:03:49,200
Hawaii?

66
00:03:49,578 --> 00:03:52,010
Yo, you can't drive to Hawaii.

67
00:03:52,157 --> 00:03:52,741
Yo.

68
00:03:52,977 --> 00:03:54,611
I know.

69
00:03:54,708 --> 00:03:57,292
I'm just saying I wish.

70
00:03:59,517 --> 00:04:01,390
Whoa, whoa.

71
00:04:01,495 --> 00:04:03,273
No, no. Don't get it.
They'll leave.

72
00:04:03,366 --> 00:04:05,430
Just let me see who it is.

73
00:04:10,206 --> 00:04:11,842
It's a cop.

74
00:04:12,078 --> 00:04:14,192
No, no, no, no, no.
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

75
00:04:17,348 --> 00:04:18,980
Sorry to disturb you, ma'am.

76
00:04:19,127 --> 00:04:21,851
Have you happened
to see this person?

77
00:04:55,617 --> 00:04:58,863
Last night we got a few phone calls
that he was spotted in the area.

78
00:04:59,138 --> 00:05:00,870
So we're going door-to-door.

79
00:05:01,668 --> 00:05:03,400
Why are you looking for him?

80
00:05:03,545 --> 00:05:06,123
He escaped from prison in
Illinois a couple of days ago.

81
00:05:06,267 --> 00:05:07,481
Have you seen him?

82
00:05:12,396 --> 00:05:14,220
No.

83
00:05:14,455 --> 00:05:16,220
He doesn't look familiar.

84
00:05:16,638 --> 00:05:17,942
Are you sure?

85
00:05:19,337 --> 00:05:21,311
Yeah. I'm sure.

86
00:05:23,626 --> 00:05:25,970
All right.
Thanks for your time.

87
00:05:31,168 --> 00:05:34,790
Whoa. Whoa, whoa, whoa.
This ain't...

88
00:05:34,937 --> 00:05:38,511
This is not what you think,
all right? Look.

89
00:05:38,697 --> 00:05:40,143
Listen to me, this...

90
00:05:40,245 --> 00:05:43,012
Just... listen. Okay?

91
00:05:43,378 --> 00:05:46,152
All I did was steal
a baseball card.

92
00:05:47,026 --> 00:05:50,180
Okay? I'm not like those
other fools up in there.

93
00:05:51,298 --> 00:05:54,401
I'm gonna go for a walk, okay?

94
00:05:54,867 --> 00:05:58,072
I'm gonna leave my
keys right here.

95
00:05:58,165 --> 00:06:02,123
And when I come back,
my car will be gone.

96
00:06:02,637 --> 00:06:07,862
I'm sure, in a few hours,
they'll find it somewhere...

97
00:06:08,186 --> 00:06:09,920
abandoned.

98
00:06:14,468 --> 00:06:17,140
Wait. Wait.

99
00:06:22,427 --> 00:06:25,433
I wish it could be different.

100
00:06:26,458 --> 00:06:27,952
I have to go.

101
00:06:46,197 --> 00:06:47,413
"Too-le."

102
00:06:47,547 --> 00:06:49,280
I think it's "To-ill-uh."

103
00:06:49,476 --> 00:06:50,731
Hell of a town.

104
00:06:51,107 --> 00:06:54,073
Small is good.
Means the ranch'll be easier to find.

105
00:06:54,217 --> 00:06:56,091
All we got to do
is get that money

106
00:06:56,558 --> 00:06:59,141
and we'll be out of
here by nightfall.

107
00:06:59,425 --> 00:07:00,212
Right.

108
00:07:20,857 --> 00:07:23,821
Oh, sir. Soil test came
back from Scofield's crash.

109
00:07:23,916 --> 00:07:26,033
Not that you need any
more proof, but...

110
00:07:26,167 --> 00:07:28,232
he really went out of
his way this time.

111
00:07:28,337 --> 00:07:29,783
What else do you have?

112
00:07:29,926 --> 00:07:32,653
Man was violently assaulted
in Nebraska by a hitchhiker

113
00:07:32,747 --> 00:07:35,811
matching Bagwell's description.
He was headed west on the I-80.

114
00:07:35,947 --> 00:07:37,820
Omaha's putting together
a photo lineup.

115
00:07:37,926 --> 00:07:39,702
What do you have on Scofield?

116
00:07:39,896 --> 00:07:42,432
What does anybody
have on Scofield?

117
00:07:43,827 --> 00:07:46,933
Uh, I've got some results
from his hard drive.

118
00:07:47,066 --> 00:07:48,992
The one recovered
from the river.

119
00:07:50,018 --> 00:07:53,642
We were able to use the sector editor to
restore the master boot. So
from that...

120
00:07:53,738 --> 00:07:56,892
I don't care how you did it.
What do you have?

121
00:07:58,275 --> 00:08:02,641
More than half the contents
of the buffer. About 60%.

122
00:08:07,685 --> 00:08:09,001
It looks pretty random.

123
00:08:09,277 --> 00:08:11,720
Print it up. All of it.
I want it on my desk.

124
00:08:15,225 --> 00:08:17,243
Well, guess what?

125
00:08:17,617 --> 00:08:20,013
No listing for a
Double K Ranch.

126
00:08:20,527 --> 00:08:23,583
Excuse me. You know where I
might find a Double K Ranch?

127
00:08:23,728 --> 00:08:26,313
- What you call it?
- Double K Ranch.

128
00:08:26,436 --> 00:08:28,453
- No.
- You from around here?

129
00:08:28,595 --> 00:08:31,931
Yeah. Born and raised.
There's no Double-nothin'.

130
00:08:32,075 --> 00:08:34,523
Great. Thank you.

131
00:08:35,728 --> 00:08:39,110
Looks like Westmoreland spent his last
breath blowing smoke up your ass.

132
00:08:39,216 --> 00:08:42,603
There's one way to find out.
The county keeps property records.

133
00:08:42,955 --> 00:08:47,192
Every plot is mapped out with
dimensions. It's public record.

134
00:08:47,428 --> 00:08:51,013
But if there is a tax
assessor's office here,

135
00:08:51,198 --> 00:08:56,191
it's gonna be in there,
the Municipal Building.

136
00:08:56,515 --> 00:08:58,962
Lots of cops in there, Michael.

137
00:09:02,997 --> 00:09:05,483
- Dispatch.
- Someone...

138
00:09:05,578 --> 00:09:07,391
someone stole my
car this morning.

139
00:09:07,487 --> 00:09:09,882
I'm at the Lotus Motel
off Interstate 80.

140
00:09:09,975 --> 00:09:11,522
Did you see who took it?

141
00:09:11,718 --> 00:09:15,340
No. I went out for a walk and
when I came back, it was gone.

142
00:09:15,435 --> 00:09:17,593
This morning?
Why didn't you call before?

143
00:09:17,826 --> 00:09:20,460
I... I don't know.

144
00:10:16,853 --> 00:10:19,820
- Mr. Kellerman.
- Mr. Kim.

145
00:10:21,581 --> 00:10:23,658
Surprised to see
you in Chicago.

146
00:10:24,186 --> 00:10:27,534
- Just looking for updates.
- Sara Tancredi. I'm on it.

147
00:10:28,039 --> 00:10:30,342
Is pursuing her the
best use of your time?

148
00:10:30,667 --> 00:10:32,641
It is.
She's in contact with Scofield.

149
00:10:32,737 --> 00:10:34,610
I was there when he
called yesterday.

150
00:10:34,938 --> 00:10:37,052
We stay with her,
she takes us right to him,

151
00:10:37,145 --> 00:10:38,510
he takes us to Burrows.

152
00:10:39,987 --> 00:10:43,001
All right.
If you're that confident.

153
00:10:43,098 --> 00:10:44,202
I am.

154
00:10:45,315 --> 00:10:49,170
- I'll let the president know.
- I contact the president directly.

155
00:10:50,246 --> 00:10:52,302
I'll contact her.

156
00:10:53,445 --> 00:10:55,420
Keep me posted.

157
00:11:21,508 --> 00:11:25,172
If you want to restore your dignity,
you need to take action.

158
00:11:25,318 --> 00:11:29,130
Making amends requires much
more than saying "I'm sorry."

159
00:11:29,278 --> 00:11:31,202
It means learning to change.

160
00:11:31,528 --> 00:11:33,731
The apology is just
the first step.

161
00:11:33,805 --> 00:11:37,720
The most important thing is
that you display honesty,

162
00:11:37,848 --> 00:11:42,790
courage and compassion when
you extend your apologies.

163
00:11:42,887 --> 00:11:45,421
You need to earn
your forgiveness.

164
00:11:46,126 --> 00:11:48,192
We'll talk about
it more on Friday.

165
00:12:02,356 --> 00:12:04,512
I've got a great idea.

166
00:12:04,658 --> 00:12:05,732
What's that?

167
00:12:05,867 --> 00:12:09,542
Since you are such a fan of lame,
store-bought blueberry pie,

168
00:12:09,687 --> 00:12:15,152
I am going to bake you a real
pie of your choice tonight.

169
00:12:16,967 --> 00:12:18,322
I can't.

170
00:12:18,736 --> 00:12:22,882
I really don't need to be seeing anyone
right now who isn't my therapist.

171
00:12:23,307 --> 00:12:25,933
I've been a hermit lately, too.

172
00:12:26,586 --> 00:12:28,512
My partner Daniel's
away on business.

173
00:12:28,608 --> 00:12:33,932
I've been sitting around every
night by myself. Kind of pathetic.

174
00:12:34,588 --> 00:12:37,692
I am so sorry.
I thought you meant...

175
00:12:38,057 --> 00:12:39,271
Um...

176
00:12:39,468 --> 00:12:40,912
I thought...

177
00:12:41,708 --> 00:12:45,941
- The pie...
- Oh, no.

178
00:12:47,017 --> 00:12:48,371
That's my ego.

179
00:12:48,467 --> 00:12:49,781
No, I was really
talking about...

180
00:12:49,866 --> 00:12:51,372
- Pie?
- Yeah. Actual blueberries.

181
00:12:51,608 --> 00:12:53,902
Like we'd make pie and
watch Fried Green Tomatoes.

182
00:12:53,996 --> 00:12:54,790
I get it, I get it.

183
00:12:54,977 --> 00:12:57,331
I'm the best ex-junkie
cook in this town.

184
00:12:57,465 --> 00:12:59,631
Thank you. I just...
I got to clean my apartment.

185
00:12:59,727 --> 00:13:02,923
It's disgusting, and I realize that
sounds like an excuse; it's not.

186
00:13:03,025 --> 00:13:04,991
No, no, no, I get it. Um...

187
00:13:05,368 --> 00:13:07,673
You do what you got to do.

188
00:13:08,455 --> 00:13:10,241
Have a good night.

189
00:13:11,355 --> 00:13:13,041
Do you deliver?

190
00:13:22,438 --> 00:13:23,703
Next batch.

191
00:13:54,246 --> 00:13:56,693
Just... put it on the desk.

192
00:13:58,896 --> 00:14:00,372
Does any of this
stuff mean anything?

193
00:14:00,448 --> 00:14:01,613
I don't know. Ask me later.

194
00:14:02,126 --> 00:14:03,712
Think he's a genius
or a whack-job?

195
00:14:03,855 --> 00:14:05,173
I think we answered
that question

196
00:14:05,356 --> 00:14:07,052
when we assigned a hundred
agents to the case.

197
00:14:07,085 --> 00:14:10,243
So why don't you go and get me the rest
of it, huh? Does that work for you?

198
00:14:41,707 --> 00:14:47,653
Alackaday. I just found
me an In-betweener.

199
00:14:49,088 --> 00:14:51,343
Where you going in
such a hurry, huh?

200
00:14:51,488 --> 00:14:53,971
- None of your beeswax, yo.
- I know where.

201
00:14:54,067 --> 00:14:56,543
Same place as every other man
who was in that room that night.

202
00:14:56,658 --> 00:15:00,423
They all comin' around here
for a big family reunion

203
00:15:00,518 --> 00:15:03,763
at the Ku Klux Ranch.
If they ain't here already.

204
00:15:04,136 --> 00:15:07,651
Ain't no country folk in this town
ever heard of the Double K Ranch.

205
00:15:07,746 --> 00:15:10,713
Seems like you've been misinformed.
Indeedy there is a Double K.

206
00:15:10,807 --> 00:15:12,740
It's just a matter of who
gets there first, all right?

207
00:15:12,778 --> 00:15:14,713
The stars are going to
collide in Tooele, my friend.

208
00:15:14,746 --> 00:15:16,953
You're going to need
me on your side.

209
00:15:17,057 --> 00:15:19,813
This ain't Fox River, all right?
I don't need any...

210
00:15:22,218 --> 00:15:26,881
As you can see... I need you.

211
00:15:28,097 --> 00:15:32,383
Get your grubby paws off me, you freak.
I ain't your ditch digger.

212
00:15:32,477 --> 00:15:34,730
I don't want nothing from you.
I don't need nothing.

213
00:15:34,826 --> 00:15:39,820
You might ...if a man knew where
he was supposed to be looking.

214
00:15:53,567 --> 00:15:59,171
Hi. Are you having the Hector Avila
and Maricruz Delgado wedding today?

215
00:15:59,455 --> 00:16:03,933
- Avila.
- No? Okay, thanks.

216
00:16:09,625 --> 00:16:14,953
Hi. Are you having the Hector Avila
and Maricruz Delgado wedding today?

217
00:16:15,097 --> 00:16:16,682
Avila.

218
00:16:17,938 --> 00:16:19,670
Delgado.

219
00:16:19,958 --> 00:16:21,403
Really?

220
00:16:22,287 --> 00:16:23,361
When?

221
00:16:34,515 --> 00:16:37,533
Stay calm.
We'll be out in ten minutes.

222
00:16:38,807 --> 00:16:41,272
One at a time. Clear.

223
00:16:42,156 --> 00:16:43,372
Back up.

224
00:16:47,258 --> 00:16:51,450
- Are you wearing a watch?
- Uh, yeah.

225
00:17:03,305 --> 00:17:04,851
Have a nice day.

226
00:17:07,216 --> 00:17:08,573
Thanks.

227
00:17:17,647 --> 00:17:19,660
This is exactly what we need.

228
00:17:19,806 --> 00:17:24,612
It's a map of every parcel of land.
Topography, buildings...

229
00:17:24,758 --> 00:17:25,870
everything.

230
00:17:29,906 --> 00:17:32,012
Karl Kokosing. Double K.

231
00:17:32,105 --> 00:17:35,883
I don't like the way this
guy is looking at us.

232
00:17:43,978 --> 00:17:45,483
1213.

233
00:17:48,485 --> 00:17:50,793
Where's 1213?

234
00:17:57,318 --> 00:17:59,432
Ms. Sebern,
I need to speak with you.

235
00:17:59,526 --> 00:18:01,833
Come on, man,
we got to roll now.

236
00:18:02,758 --> 00:18:04,350
Ms. Sebern.

237
00:18:04,498 --> 00:18:06,232
Come on. You got the map?

238
00:18:10,167 --> 00:18:11,663
No.

239
00:18:12,775 --> 00:18:14,563
Someone else does.

240
00:18:20,765 --> 00:18:23,771
Someone got here before us.
It's the only explanation.

241
00:18:29,706 --> 00:18:31,581
Son of a bitch is still alive.

242
00:18:34,418 --> 00:18:35,820
Hey, pretty!

243
00:18:36,056 --> 00:18:39,991
What are you going to do,
scream, man?

244
00:18:41,476 --> 00:18:44,110
How the hell...
are you still breathing?

245
00:18:44,388 --> 00:18:46,640
What the hell did
you do to your hand?

246
00:18:48,446 --> 00:18:50,211
Easy, easy...

247
